  • I think condition1 and condition2 are norminal based on the description.
# exter_cond variable
# ExterCond: Evaluates the present condition of the material on the exterior
# Ex    Excellent Gd    Good TA Average/Typical Fa  Fair Po Poor
all_data %<>% 
  mutate(exter_cond = as_factor(exter_cond),
         exter_cond = fct_relevel(exter_cond,
              c("Po", "Fa", "TA", "Gd", "Ex")),
         exter_cond = as.numeric(exter_cond))
# bsmt_cond
# BsmtCond: Evaluates the general condition of the basement
# Ex    Excellent
# Gd    Good
# TA    Typical - slight dampness allowed
# Fa    Fair - dampness or some cracking or settling
# Po    Poor - Severe cracking, settling, or wetness
# NA    No Basement
all_data %<>% 
  mutate(bsmt_cond = as_factor(bsmt_cond),
         bsmt_cond = fct_explicit_na(bsmt_cond,
                                     na_level="No"),
         bsmt_cond = fct_relevel(bsmt_cond,
              c("No", "Po", "Fa", "TA", "Gd", "Ex")),
         bsmt_cond = as.numeric(bsmt_cond))

4.3 New variables

all_data %<>% 
  mutate(old = yr_sold - year_built,
         old_remodel = yr_sold - year_remod_add,
         house_area = gr_liv_area + total_bsmt_sf,
         total_area = house_area + garage_area,
         total_area_w_pool = total_area + pool_area,
         house_area_ratio = total_area_w_pool / lot_area,
         extra_area = lot_area - total_area_w_pool,
         overall_plus = overall_qual + overall_cond,
         overall_multi = overall_qual * overall_cond,
         overall_square = overall_qual^2 + overall_cond^2,
         overall_minus = overall_qual - overall_cond,
         overall_gr_grage_inter = overall_qual * garage_area * gr_liv_area,
         garage_weighted_qual = garage_cars * garage_qual,
         garage_weighted_cond = garage_cars * garage_cond,
         garage_overall = garage_qual + garage_cond
         )

5.1 Missing values

5.1.1 General info.

na_info <- all_data %>% 
  map_df(~sum(is.na(.))) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = everything(), 
               names_to = "variable",
               values_to = "na_count") %>% 
  arrange(desc(na_count))
na_info %>% DT::datatable(width = "100%")
skewed_col <- all_data %>% 
  select(-c(sale_price, ms_sub_class)) %>% 
  summarise(across(where(is.numeric), 
             ~moments::skewness(.x, na.rm = T))) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = everything(),
               names_to = "variable",
               values_to = "skewness") %>% 
  filter(abs(skewness) > 1) %>% 
  select(variable) %>% unlist() %>% as.vector()

5.2 Make recipe

source("robust.R")

housing_recipe <- all_data %>% 
  recipe(sale_price ~ .) %>%
  step_mutate(ms_sub_class = factor(ms_sub_class)) %>% 
  step_rm(id) %>% 
  step_log(sale_price, offset = 1) %>%
  step_log(all_of(skewed_col), offset = 1) %>%
  step_unknown(all_of(col_w_unknown)) %>% 
  step_modeimpute(all_nominal()) %>% 
  step_integer(all_nominal()) %>% 
  # step_corr(all_predictors(), threshold = 0.3) %>% 
  # step_dummy(all_of(nominal_col), one_hot = T) %>% 
  step_meanimpute(all_numeric(), -all_outcomes()) %>%
  step_center(all_predictors()) %>%
  prep(training = all_data)
## Warning in bake.step_log(x$steps[[i]], new_data = training): NaNs produced
print(housing_recipe)

We are done for preprocessing. Let’s split the data set.

train_index <- seq_len(nrow(train))
train2 <- all_data2[train_index,]
test2 <- all_data2[-train_index,]

6 Split the train into validation and train

set.seed(2021)

# validation_split <- validation_split(train2, prop = 0.7)
validation_split <- vfold_cv(train2, v = 10, strata = sale_price)

# actual split id stored in the following
# validation_split$splits[[1]]$in_id
# the whole point is that it's there and trust tidymodels :)
# head(validation_split$splits[[1]]$in_id)

7 Set the tuning spec

tune_spec <- rand_forest(mtry = tune(),
                         min_n = tune(),
                         trees = 1000) %>% 
    set_engine("ranger") %>% 
    set_mode("regression")

param_grid <- grid_random(finalize(mtry(), x = train2[,-1]),
                          min_n(),
                          size = 100)

8 Set workflow()

workflow <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(tune_spec) %>% 
  add_formula(sale_price ~ .)

9 Tuning trees

library(doParallel)
Cluster <- makeCluster(detectCores() - 1)
registerDoParallel(Cluster)

library(tictoc)
tic()
tune_result <- workflow %>% 
  tune_grid(validation_split,
            grid = param_grid,
            metrics = metric_set(rmse))

11 Set Elastic net regression model and fitting

mixture parameter determines the proportion of Lasso regression in the Elastic net.

cores <- parallel::detectCores() -1
cores
## [1] 19
rf_model <- 
  rand_forest(mtry = tune_best$mtry,
              min_n = tune_best$min_n,
              trees = 1000) %>% 
    set_engine("ranger", seed = 2021, num.threads = cores) %>% 
    set_mode("regression")

tic()
rf_fit <- 
    rf_model %>% 
    fit(sale_price ~ ., data = train2)
toc()
